# Language Conventions

## Code → English

All code identifiers and technical content must be in **English**:
- Function and variable names
- folders
- Component names, file names
- Comments, documentation (JSDoc, README)
- Error messages in logs (for developers)
- Database identifiers (tables, columns)
- API routes and keys

```typescript
// ✅ GOOD
function getPatientsByUserPhone(userPhone: string) { }
const patientList = [];
<PatientForm onSubmit={handleSubmit} />

// ❌ BAD
function obterPacientesPorTelefone(telefoneUsuario: string) { }
const listaDePacientes = [];
<PacienteFormulario onSubmit={handleSubmit} />
```

## Copy → Português (Brasil)

All user-facing text must be in **Brazilian Portuguese**:
- UI labels, placeholders, buttons
- Validation messages shown to users
- Page titles, headings
- Toast/notification messages
- Email templates

```tsx
// ✅ GOOD
<Button>Salvar</Button>
<Input placeholder="Digite o nome do paciente" />
<p>Nenhum paciente encontrado.</p>

// ❌ BAD
<Button>Save</Button>
<Input placeholder="Enter patient name" />
<p>No patients found.</p>
```

## Summary

| Context | Language |
|---------|----------|
| Code (identifiers, comments) | English |
| User-facing copy (UI, messages) | Português (Brasil) |
